    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Rhodiola humilis are its antioxidant capabilities, which protect against cell damage and oxidative stress. This is largely due to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids, which contribute to its anti-inflammatory effects by modulating pro-inflammatory enzymes. The antimicrobial properties of Rhodiola humilis are attributed to the presence of saponins and terpenoids, which inhibit the growth of microorganisms and prevent infections. Additionally, Rhodiola humilis exhibits neuroprotective effects, which are thought to be mediated by the action of phenylethylamine and other alkaloids that promote neuronal health and survival. Moreover, Rhodiola humilis has adaptogenic properties, allowing it to help the body adapt to stress and promote balance in physiological functions, which is often associated with the presence of glycosides and other bioactive compounds.",
