    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Rhodiola humilis improperly include inducing nausea, experience nausea, developing insomnia, experiencing dizziness, and causing insomnia. These side effects are attributed to the fact that Rhodiola humilis contains bioactive compounds that may interact with certain medications or exacerbate underlying health conditions. The improper use of Rhodiola humilis may also lead to overstimulation, particularly when consumed in high doses or combined with other stimulants. Furthermore, Rhodiola humilis may not be suitable for individuals with anxiety disorders, as it can worsen symptoms and make it difficult to fall asleep. Additionally, the lack of standardization and quality control in Rhodiola humilis products may contribute to the risk of adverse reactions.",
