    "taxonomy": "Rhodiola humilis is classified in the family Crassulaceae. It belongs to the genus Rhodiola and is a species of flowering plant. Rhodiola humilis is native to the mountainous regions of the northern hemisphere and is commonly found in alpine and subalpine habitats. This plant is part of the Rhodiola genus, which comprises several other species, including Rhodiola rosea. Rhodiola humilis is a perennial plant that thrives in well-drained soil and full sun exposure.",
