    "intro": "Rhodiola humilis, also known as low-lying rhodiola, is a perennial plant species belonging to the Crassulaceae family, native to the mountainous regions of Central Asia. Rhodiola humilis is valued for its adaptogenic properties, which provide a range of health benefits, including reducing stress and fatigue, improving mental clarity and mood, and enhancing physical performance and endurance. The plant's bioactive constituents, including rosavin, salidroside, and tyrosol, are responsible for its adaptogenic and medicinal properties. In traditional medicine, Rhodiola humilis is commonly prepared as a tea, tincture, or capsule, and is often used to promote relaxation, improve sleep quality, and boost cognitive function."
